    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PUSCH power control handling in TDD configurations\n\n### Summary\nThe PUSCH power control implementation was not properly handling TDD configurations where the uplink and downlink assignments change dynamically. This caused incorrect power calculations leading to reduced throughput and increased BLER in TDD scenarios.\n\nThe issue was traced to the power control calculation not accounting for the TDD uplink/downlink configuration when determining the pathloss reference.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_power_control.c`: Modified `get_pusch_power_ue` to properly handle TDD configurations\n- `openair1/PHY/defs_nr_UE.h`: Added TDD configuration parameters to power control structure\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure UE for TDD operation with dynamic uplink/downlink switching\n2. Run downlink throughput test in varying channel conditions\n3. Observe higher than expected BLER and reduced throughput compared to FDD\n4. Power control debug logs show incorrect pathloss calculations\n\n"
}